{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ve23w4pb6vWoPqt26CF9Wr","type":"tool_result","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-04-02\n\n### 1-1-delete-beads-integration — create-story (2026-04-02T07:58)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `_bmad/bmm/config.yaml` was at `_bmad/config.yaml` — required a glob to find it\n- workflow.md file referenced in skill trigger was actually workflow.yaml — minor naming inconsistency\n\n**Workarounds applied:** None significant.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- Some dependent files (bridge.ts, sync.ts, retro-import.ts, github-import.ts) may have their primary functionality gutted when beads calls are removed\n- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` and `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` call `isBeadsInitialized` / `listIssues` — these may be in hot paths\n\n**Observations:**\n- Beads dependency graph is larger than epics-v2 doc suggests (25+ files total including tests)\n- All 8 ACs are `test-provable` — pure code-deletion story\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: 16\n- By tool: Bash: 4, Read: 8, Glob: 4, Grep: 1, Write: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs: `ls implementation-artifacts/` (~190 lines), `git log` (~5 lines)\n- Files read: 8 unique, 8 total reads\n- Redundant operations: None\n\n### 1-1-delete-beads-integration — dev-story (2026-04-02T08:15)\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- `init-project.test.ts` had `mockIsBeadsInitialized` in a `beforeEach` block not adjacent to mock declaration — required second test fix pass\n- `status.test.ts` had health check test asserting `[OK] Beads: available` missed in first pass\n- `retro-import.test.ts` and `github-import.test.ts` deeply intertwined with beads mocks — full rewrites necessary\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- Added local `BeadsIssue` interface in `src/lib/sync/story-files.ts` (import source was deleted)\n- `epic-generator.test.ts` uses `describe.skip` for removed `importOnboardingEpic` test suite\n- `storyToGapId` in `onboard-checks.ts` reimplemented