{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012984xrqUv6qXBw2yMZaWbb","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\tstepsCompleted: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 8]\n3\tlastStep: 8\n4\tstatus: 'complete'\n5\tcompletedAt: '2026-04-02'\n6\tinputDocuments:\n7\t  - prd-evaluator-redesign.md\n8\t  - research/domain-harness-design-long-running-agents-research-2026-04-01.md\n9\t  - research/technical-ai-agent-verification-testing-research-2026-03-16.md\n10\t  - research/technical-workflow-engine-implementation-research-2026-04-02.md\n11\t  - architecture.md (v1 architecture, brownfield context)\n12\tworkflowType: 'architecture'\n13\tproject_name: 'codeharness'\n14\tuser_name: 'BMad'\n15\tdate: '2026-04-02'\n16\t---\n17\t\n18\t# Architecture Decision Document\n19\t\n20\t_This document builds collaboratively through step-by-step discovery. Sections are appended as we work through each architectural decision together._\n21\t\n22\t## Project Context Analysis\n23\t\n24\t### Requirements Overview\n25\t\n26\t**Functional Requirements:** 43 FRs across 10 capability areas — Workflow Definition (6), Agent Configuration (6), Workflow Configuration (3), Workflow Execution (8), Adversarial Verification (5), Feedback Loop (3), Circuit Breaker (4), Observability (2), CLI Commands (4), Legacy Removal (2).\n27\t\n28\t**Non-Functional Requirements:** 18 NFRs across Performance (5), Reliability (5), Integration (4), Code Quality (4). Architecture-critical NFRs: crash recovery via state persistence (NFR6-8), programmatic agent dispatch only (NFR11), optional observability (NFR14).\n29\t\n30\t**Scale & Complexity:**\n31\t- Primary domain: Developer tooling (CLI + plugin)\n32\t- Complexity level: High\n33\t- Estimated architectural components: ~10\n34\t- Cross-cutting concerns: config resolution chain, trace ID propagation, crash recovery, evaluator isolation\n35\t\n36\t### Technical Constraints & Dependencies\n37\t\n38\t- Runtime: Node.js (TypeScript)\n39\t- Dependencies: `commander`, `yaml`, `@anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk`\n40\t- Execution substrate: Agent SDK `query()` — async generator, session management, JSON schema output\n41\t- State: Single `workflow-state.yaml` in repo (beads-level simplicity)\n42\t- Evaluator isolation: Separate workspace, no source code, Docker container for artifact\n43\t- Docker: Required for evaluator but graceful degradation if missing (Journey 5)\n44\t\n45\t### Cross-Cutting Concerns\n46\t\n47\t1. **Config resolution** — every agent/workflow dispatch resolves embedded → user → project patches\n48\t2. **Trace ID propagation** — generated per iteration, injected into agent prompts, correlates to observability\n49\t3. **Crash recovery** — state persisted after each task, engine resumes from last checkpoint\n50\t4. **Evaluator isolation** — separate workspace, `disallowedTools` enforcement, `source_access: false`\n51\t\n52\t## Starter Template Evaluation\n53\t\n54\t### Primary Technology Domain\n55\t\n56\tCLI developer tool — Node.js/TypeScript. Brownfield project with established toolchain.\n57\t\n58\t### Starter Options: Not Applicable (Brownfield)\n59\t\n60\tExisting project toolchain is retained:\n61\t\n62\t| Decision | Current (Keep) | Source |\n63\t|----------|---------------|--------|\n64\t| Language | TypeScript (strict) | Existing project |\n65\t| Build | tsup | Existing project |\n66\t| Test | vitest (unit) + BATS (integration) | Existing project |\n67\t| CLI | commander | Existing project |\n68\t| YAML | yaml package | Existing project |\n69\t| **New** | @anthropic-ai/claude-agent-sdk | Research — replaces bash spawn |\n70\t\n71\t**No starter template needed.** One new dependency added. Internals reworked.\n72\t\n73\t## Core Architectural Decisions\n74\t\n75\t### Decision Priority Analysis\n76\t\n77\t**Critical Decisions (Block Implementation):**\n78\t1. Module boundaries — what code goes where\n79\t2. Evaluator workspace isolation — how to enforce source-free verification\n80\t3. Evaluator verdict schema — the contract between evaluator and engine\n81\t\n82\t**Important Decisions (Shape Architecture):**\n83\t4. Embedded template storage — where agent/workflow YAML files live in the package\n84\t5. Config resolution caching — resolve once or every dispatch\n85\t\n86\t**Deferred Decisions (Post-MVP):**\n87\t- PersonaNexus trait compilation algorithm (Growth phase)\n88\t- Pluggable evaluator strategies interface (Growth phase)\n89\t- Workflow marketplace format/registry (Vision phase)\n90\t\n91\t### AD1: Module Boundaries\n92\t\n93\t| Module | Responsibility | Key FRs |\n94\t|--------|---------------|---------|\n95\t| `workflow-parser` | Parse YAML, validate against JSON schema, resolve patches (embedded→user→project) | FR1-6, FR13-15 |\n96\t| `agent-resolver` | Resolve agent config through patch chain, compile to SDK inline subagent definition | FR7-12 |\n97\t| `workflow-engine` | Execute flow steps, manage iterations, handle `loop:` blocks, inject evaluator findings into retries | FR16-18, FR29-31 |\n98\t| `agent-dispatch` | Call Agent SDK `query()`, manage sessions (fresh/continue), inject trace IDs | FR19-23 |\n99\t| `evaluator` | Blind evaluator workspace setup, spawn, JSON verdict parsing | FR24-28 |\n100\t| `circuit-breaker` | Score-based stagnation detection, score history tracking | FR32-35 |\n101\t| `workflow-state` | Read/write workflow-state.yaml, crash recovery (resume from last completed task) | NFR6-8 |\n102\t\n103\t**Rationale:** 7 modules, each 100-200 LOC. Feedback loop (FR29-30) is part of `workflow-engine` — it's loop logic, not a separate concern. CLI commands (`init`, `run`, `validate`, `status`) are thin wrappers calling these modules. Observability (FR36-37) is a cross-cutting concern handled by trace ID injection in `agent-dispatch`, not a separate module.\n104\t\n105\t### AD2: Evaluator Workspace Isolation\n106\t\n107\t**Decision:** Temp directory with only story files + Docker access.\n108\t\n109\t```\n110\t/tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}/\n111\t  story-files/     # copied ACs from sprint\n112\t  verdict/         # evaluator writes JSON verdict here\n113\t```\n114\t\n115\tEngine copies story files to temp dir, spawns evaluator with `cwd` set to this directory. Agent SDK options enforce isolation:\n116\t- `bare: true` — no plugins, hooks, MCP, memory\n117\t- `disallowedTools: [\"Edit\", \"Write\"]` — read-only + execute only\n118\t- `cwd: /tmp/codeharness-verify-{runId}` — no source code present\n119\t\n120\t**Rationale:** Simplest approach. Source isn't there because we never put it there. No git worktree complexity, no Docker-in-Docker. The Agent SDK's `cwd` + `disallowedTools` provide sufficient isolation.\n121\t\n122\t### AD3: Embedded Template Storage\n123\t\n124\t**Decision:** `templates/` directory in the npm package.\n125\t\n126\t```\n127\ttemplates/\n128\t  agents/\n129\t    dev.yaml\n130\t    qa.yaml\n131\t    architect.yaml\n132\t    pm.yaml\n133\t    sm.yaml\n134\t    analyst.yaml\n135\t    ux-designer.yaml\n136\t    tech-writer.yaml\n137\t    evaluator.yaml\n138\t  workflows/\n139\t    default.yaml\n140\t```\n141\t\n142\tIncluded via `package.json` `files` array. Readable, editable for debugging, consistent with existing pattern (`templates/Dockerfile.verify`).\n143\t\n144\t**Rationale:** Files over compiled strings. Easier to inspect, diff, and debug. The `codeharness init` command copies the default workflow to the project; embedded agents are resolved at runtime from the package location.\n145\t\n146\t### AD4: Config Resolution Caching\n147\t\n148\t**Decision:** Resolve all configs once at engine startup, cache in memory.\n149\t\n150\tOn `codeharness run`:\n151\t1. Resolve workflow: load embedded → apply user patch → apply project patch → cache\n152\t2. Resolve all referenced agents: same resolution chain → cache\n153\t3. Run engine with cached configs — no file I/O during execution\n154\t\n155\t**Rationale:** Config files don't change during a run. Caching guarantees NFR2 (<200ms resolution) and eliminates repeated file system reads during long-running execution.\n156\t\n157\t### AD5: Evaluator Verdict Schema\n158\t\n159\t**Decision:** Structured JSON enforced by Agent SDK `jsonSchema` option.\n160\t\n161\t```typescript\n162\tinterface EvaluatorVerdict {\n163\t  verdict: 'pass' | 'fail';\n164\t  score: {\n165\t    passed: number;\n166\t    failed: number;\n167\t    unknown: number;\n168\t    total: number;\n169\t  };\n170\t  findings: Array<{\n171\t    ac: number;\n172\t    description: string;\n173\t    status: 'pass' | 'fail' | 'unknown';\n174\t    evidence: {\n175\t      commands_run: string[];\n176\t      output_observed: string;\n177\t      reasoning: string;\n178\t    };\n179\t  }>;\n180\t  evaluator_trace_id: string;\n181\t  duration_seconds: number;\n182\t}\n183\t```\n184\t\n185\t**Rationale:** Replaces the 175-line proof document regex parser entirely. The Agent SDK validates the output against this schema — if the evaluator doesn't produce valid JSON, the SDK rejects it. Every AC verdict requires evidence (commands + output), enforcing the anti-leniency principle structurally.\n186\t\n187\t### Decision Impact Analysis\n188\t\n189\t**Implementation Sequence:**\n190\t1. `workflow-state` — foundation for crash recovery, needed by everything\n191\t2. `workflow-parser` — parse YAML + resolve patches, needed before execution\n192\t3. `agent-resolver` — resolve agent configs, needed before dispatch\n193\t4. `agent-dispatch` — SDK integration, needed before engine can run\n194\t5. `workflow-engine` — orchestrates everything above\n195\t6. `evaluator` — depends on dispatch + state\n196\t7. `circuit-breaker` — depends on evaluator verdicts\n197\t\n198\t**Cross-Component Dependencies:**\n199\t- `workflow-engine` depends on all other modules\n200\t- `evaluator` depends on `agent-dispatch` (for SDK spawn) and `workflow-state` (for verdict recording)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CKEf3EfMT3thydJ11XftFt","session_id":"aeb5b1ee-06a7-4bdc-8279-6cd22d306d14","uuid":"b7d586b6-35ee-4d71-92d9-694508fed849","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:42:07.264Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HJJwNLWRUQ58QeogP89RRC","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 1.2: Delete Ralph Loop & Legacy Verification\n2\t\n3\tStatus: verifying\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want the Ralph bash loop, old hooks, and proof document system deleted,\n9\tSo that only the new architecture's code paths exist.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** the `ralph/` directory exists with 23+ files (ralph.sh, drivers/, lib/, logs/, state files)\n14\t   **When** the entire `ralph/` directory is deleted\n15\t   **Then** `ralph/` directory no longer exists on disk\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** the `hooks/` directory exists with 5 files (4 bash hooks + hooks.json)\n19\t   **When** the entire `hooks/` directory is deleted\n20\t   **Then** `hooks/` directory no longer exists on disk\n21\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n22\t\n23\t3. **Given** `src/lib/verifier-session.ts`, `src/lib/patch-engine.ts`, `src/lib/retry-state.ts`, and `src/lib/state.ts` exist\n24\t   **When** all four legacy lib modules are deleted\n25\t   **Then** none of these files exist on disk\n26\t   **And** their corresponding test files are also deleted (`src/lib/__tests__/patch-engine.test.ts`, `src/lib/__tests__/retry-state.test.ts`, `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verifier-session.test.ts`)\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` and `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` exist\n30\t   **When** both legacy template files are deleted\n31\t   **Then** neither file exists on disk\n32\t   **And** their corresponding test files are also deleted (`src/templates/__tests__/showboat-template.test.ts`, `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-prompt.test.ts`, `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts`)\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` and `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` exist\n36\t   **When** both ralph agent modules are deleted\n37\t   **Then** neither file exists on disk\n38\t   **And** their corresponding test files are also deleted (`src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts`, `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts`)\n39\t   **And** `src/lib/agents/index.ts` no longer re-exports ralph symbols\n40\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n41\t\n42\t6. **Given** `src/commands/retry.ts` exists\n43\t   **When** the retry command is deleted\n44\t   **Then** the file no longer exists on disk\n45\t   **And** its test file `src/commands/__tests__/retry.test.ts` is also deleted\n46\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n47\t\n48\t7. **Given** dependent files import from deleted modules (verifier-session, patch-engine, retry-state, showboat-template, verify-prompt, ralph, ralph-prompt)\n49\t   **When** all imports of deleted modules are removed from dependent files\n50\t   **Then** `grep -r \"from.*(verifier-session|patch-engine|retry-state|verify-prompt|showboat-template|ralph-prompt|ralph)\" src/ --include=\"*.ts\"` returns zero matches (excluding AGENTS.md docs)\n51\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n52\t\n53\t8. **Given** all legacy files and imports are removed\n54\t   **When** `npm run build` is executed\n55\t   **Then** the build succeeds with exit code 0\n56\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n57\t\n58\t9. **Given** all legacy files and imports are removed\n59\t   **When** `npm run test:unit` is executed\n60\t   **Then** all unit tests pass\n61\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n62\t\n63\t10. **Given** the codebase after all deletions\n64\t    **When** searching for shell scripts in the execution path\n65\t    **Then** zero `.sh` files remain under `src/` or any directory referenced by the build/runtime execution path\n66\t    **And** `find src/ -name \"*.sh\"` returns zero results\n67\t    <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n68\t\n69\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n70\t\n71\t- [x] Task 1: Delete ralph/ directory (AC: #1)\n72\t  - [x] Delete entire `ralph/` directory recursively (ralph.sh, drivers/, lib/, logs/, state files, AGENTS.md)\n73\t  - [x] Update `.gitignore` if it has ralph-specific entries\n74\t\n75\t- [x] Task 2: Delete hooks/ directory (AC: #2)\n76\t  - [x] Delete entire `hooks/` directory recursively (post-test-verify.sh, post-write-check.sh, session-start.sh, time-warning.sh, hooks.json, AGENTS.txt)\n77\t\n78\t- [x] Task 3: Delete legacy lib modules (AC: #3)\n79\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/verifier-session.ts`\n80\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/patch-engine.ts`\n81\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/retry-state.ts`\n82\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/state.ts`\n83\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/__tests__/patch-engine.test.ts`\n84\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/__tests__/retry-state.test.ts`\n85\t  - [x] Delete `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verifier-session.test.ts`\n86\t\n87\t- [x] Task 4: Delete legacy template files (AC: #4)\n88\t  - [x] Delete `src/templates/showboat-template.ts`\n89\t  - [x] Delete `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`\n90\t  - [x] Delete `src/templates/__tests__/showboat-template.test.ts`\n91\t  - [x] Delete `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-prompt.test.ts`\n92\t  - [x] Delete `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts`\n93\t\n94\t- [x] Task 5: Delete ralph agent modules (AC: #5)\n95\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts`\n96\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts`\n97\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts`\n98\t  - [x] Delete `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts`\n99\t  - [x] Remove ralph re-exports from `src/lib/agents/index.ts` (RalphDriver, RalphConfig, buildSpawnArgs, resolveRalphPath, parseRalphMessage, parseIterationMessage, generateRalphPrompt, RalphPromptConfig)\n100\t\n101\t- [x] Task 6: Delete retry command (AC: #6)\n102\t  - [x] Delete `src/commands/retry.ts`\n103\t  - [x] Delete `src/commands/__tests__/retry.test.ts`\n104\t\n105\t- [x] Task 7: Remove imports of deleted modules from dependent files (AC: #7)\n106\t  - [x] `src/lib/bmad.ts` — remove `applyPatch` import from `patch-engine.js`; keep non-patch-engine logic\n107\t  - [x] `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — remove `showboatProofTemplate` and `AcceptanceCriterion` imports from `showboat-template.js`\n108\t  - [x] `src/commands/run.ts` — remove `generateRalphPrompt` import from `ralph-prompt.js`; refactor to use workflow-engine call instead\n109\t  - [x] `src/commands/teardown.ts` — remove `removePatch` import from `patch-engine.js`\n110\t  - [x] `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — remove `parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage` imports from `ralph.js`\n111\t  - [x] `src/lib/dashboard-formatter.ts` — remove any ralph-specific formatting logic if present\n112\t\n113\t- [x] Task 8: Fix test files that mock deleted modules (AC: #9)\n114\t  - [x] `src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts` — remove `removePatch` mock from `patch-engine.js`\n115\t  - [x] `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — remove `generateRalphPrompt` mock from `ralph-prompt.js`\n116\t  - [x] `src/lib/__tests__/run-helpers.test.ts` — remove ralph import mocks\n117\t  - [x] `src/lib/__tests__/dashboard-formatter.test.ts` — remove ralph-specific test cases if any\n118\t\n119\t- [x] Task 9: Verify build and tests pass (AC: #8, #9, #10)\n120\t  - [x] Run `npm run build` and confirm exit 0\n121\t  - [x] Run `npm run test:unit` and confirm all pass\n122\t  - [x] Run `find src/ -name \"*.sh\"` and confirm zero results\n123\t\n124\t## Dev Notes\n125\t\n126\t### Surgical Removal Strategy\n127\t\n128\tThe architecture document (architecture-v2.md) explicitly lists this as priority #2 after beads cleanup: **\"Legacy deletion (ralph/, hooks/, old verify/proof modules).\"** Story 1.1 (beads cleanup) is already done, so this story can proceed.\n129\t\n130\tDelete entire directories first (ralph/, hooks/), then delete individual source files, then fix all compiler errors in one pass. Do NOT attempt to build between deletions — do all deletions atomically.\n131\t\n132\t### What to Do with Functions That Called Deleted Modules\n133\t\n134\tWhen a function's sole purpose was to call a deleted module (e.g., `applyPatch` in bmad.ts, `generateRalphPrompt` in run.ts):\n135\t- If the function has no other logic, **remove it entirely** or replace with a `// TODO: v2 workflow-engine (Epic 5)` comment\n136\t- If the function has mixed logic, **keep the non-legacy lines** and remove only the deleted-module calls\n137\t- The `run.ts` command is a REWORK target (Epic 5) — for now, remove the Ralph spawn and leave a placeholder\n138\t\n139\t### Key risk: run.ts depends heavily on Ralph\n140\t\n141\t`src/commands/run.ts` imports `generateRalphPrompt` and likely orchestrates the Ralph bash loop. Removing Ralph from run.ts may leave it non-functional. This is expected — Epic 5 (Story 5.4) will rebuild `codeharness run` to use the workflow engine. For this story, remove Ralph references and leave a stub or TODO.\n142\t\n143\t### Files That Import Deleted Modules — Complete Dependency Map\n144\t\n145\t**Directories to delete entirely:**\n146\t- `ralph/` — 23+ files (bash loop, drivers, lib, logs, state)\n147\t- `hooks/` — 5 files (4 bash hooks + hooks.json)\n148\t\n149\t**Source files to delete (from src/lib/):**\n150\t- `src/lib/verifier-session.ts` — old black-box verifier session spawner\n151\t- `src/lib/patch-engine.ts` — BMAD patch engine (will be rebuilt in v2)\n152\t- `src/lib/retry-state.ts` — legacy retry/flagged state management\n153\t- `src/lib/state.ts` — old state module (replaced by workflow-state in Story 1.3)\n154\t\n155\t**Source files to delete (from src/templates/):**\n156\t- `src/templates/showboat-template.ts` — proof document format (replaced by JSON verdict in Epic 6)\n157\t- `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — black-box verifier prompt (replaced by evaluator agent YAML in Epic 6)\n158\t\n159\t**Source files to delete (from src/lib/agents/):**\n160\t- `src/lib/agents/ralph.ts` — Ralph driver and parser\n161\t- `src/lib/agents/ralph-prompt.ts` — Ralph loop prompt generator\n162\t\n163\t**Source files to delete (from src/commands/):**\n164\t- `src/commands/retry.ts` — retry command (merged into workflow-state in Epic 5)\n165\t\n166\t**Dependents (surgical cleanup):**\n167\t- `src/lib/bmad.ts` — imports `applyPatch` from `patch-engine.js`\n168\t- `src/modules/verify/orchestrator.ts` — imports `showboatProofTemplate`, `AcceptanceCriterion` from `showboat-template.js`\n169\t- `src/commands/run.ts` — imports `generateRalphPrompt` from `ralph-prompt.js`\n170\t- `src/commands/teardown.ts` — imports `removePatch` from `patch-engine.js`\n171\t- `src/lib/run-helpers.ts` — imports `parseRalphMessage`, `parseIterationMessage` from `ralph.js`\n172\t- `src/lib/agents/index.ts` — barrel re-exports ralph symbols\n173\t\n174\t**Test files to delete:**\n175\t- `src/lib/__tests__/patch-engine.test.ts`\n176\t- `src/lib/__tests__/retry-state.test.ts`\n177\t- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verifier-session.test.ts`\n178\t- `src/templates/__tests__/showboat-template.test.ts`\n179\t- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-prompt.test.ts`\n180\t- `src/modules/verify/__tests__/verification-observability-patch.test.ts`\n181\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph.test.ts`\n182\t- `src/lib/agents/__tests__/ralph-prompt.test.ts`\n183\t- `src/commands/__tests__/retry.test.ts`\n184\t\n185\t**Test files to update (remove mocks):**\n186\t- `src/commands/__tests__/teardown.test.ts`\n187\t- `src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts`\n188\t- `src/lib/__tests__/run-helpers.test.ts`\n189\t- `src/lib/__tests__/dashboard-formatter.test.ts`\n190\t\n191\t### Architecture Compliance\n192\t\n193\t- **FR48:** System does not contain Ralph bash loop, session flags, proof parsers, self-verify hooks, beads\n194\t- **FR49:** System has exactly one verification path: blind evaluator session\n195\t- **NFR16:** Zero shell scripts in execution path\n196\t- **NFR17:** Net negative LOC after legacy removal — this story should delete significantly more lines than it adds\n197\t- **Anti-pattern:** Do NOT create replacements in this story. Ralph replacement is Epic 5 (workflow engine). Verify replacement is Epic 6 (blind evaluator). Proof replacement is Epic 6 (JSON verdict).\n198\t\n199\t### Testing Standards\n200\t\n201\t- After cleanup, `npm run build` must succeed (zero references to deleted modules in compiled output)\n202\t- After cleanup, `npm run test:unit` must pass\n203\t- No new tests required for this story — it is pure deletion\n204\t- Test files that mock deleted modules must have those mocks removed; remaining test logic should still assert non-legacy behavior\n205\t\n206\t### References\n207\t\n208\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 1.2: Delete Ralph Loop & Legacy Verification]\n209\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#DELETE — Entire Files]\n210\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Dependency Chain Breaks to Handle]\n211\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Priority]\n212\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#FR48, FR49]\n213\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01CKEf3EfMT3thydJ11XftFt","session_id":"aeb5b1ee-06a7-4bdc-8279-6cd22d306d14","uuid":"f6395619-561a-4b5d-be27-186ce607a515","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:42:07.619Z"}
