{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01P4pcLce3LK4b96EteE5BuZ","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Story 1.3: Workflow State Module\n2\t\n3\tStatus: ready-for-dev\n4\t\n5\t## Story\n6\t\n7\tAs a developer,\n8\tI want a workflow-state module that persists execution state to YAML,\n9\tso that the engine can resume from the last completed task after a crash.\n10\t\n11\t## Acceptance Criteria\n12\t\n13\t1. **Given** no `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` exists\n14\t   **When** `writeState()` is called after a task completion\n15\t   **Then** `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` is created with all required fields: `workflow_name` (string), `started` (ISO timestamp), `iteration` (number), `phase` (string), `tasks_completed` (array of task checkpoint objects), `evaluator_scores` (array of score objects), and `circuit_breaker` (object with `triggered`, `reason`, `score_history`)\n16\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n17\t\n18\t2. **Given** a valid `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` exists on disk\n19\t   **When** `readState()` is called\n20\t   **Then** the returned object matches the `WorkflowState` TypeScript interface with all fields correctly typed\n21\t   **And** round-trip fidelity is preserved: `readState(writeState(state))` returns an equivalent object\n22\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n23\t\n24\t3. **Given** a workflow-state.yaml was written by a previous process\n25\t   **When** the process exits and a new process calls `readState()`\n26\t   **Then** the previously written state is returned intact (state survives process exit)\n27\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n28\t\n29\t4. **Given** a corrupted or invalid YAML file at `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`\n30\t   **When** `readState()` is called\n31\t   **Then** it returns a default empty state (not throw) so the engine can start fresh\n32\t   **And** the corrupted file is not silently ignored — a warning is emitted via the `warn()` output utility\n33\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n34\t\n35\t5. **Given** the `.codeharness/` directory does not exist\n36\t   **When** `writeState()` is called\n37\t   **Then** the directory is created automatically before writing the file\n38\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n39\t\n40\t6. **Given** concurrent or rapid sequential `writeState()` calls\n41\t   **When** each call provides a different state\n42\t   **Then** the file always contains a complete, valid YAML document (no partial writes)\n43\t   **And** the last write wins\n44\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n45\t\n46\t7. **Given** the workflow-state module source file\n47\t   **When** unit tests are run via `npm run test:unit`\n48\t   **Then** all tests pass with 80%+ code coverage on `src/lib/workflow-state.ts`\n49\t   **And** tests cover: read, write, crash recovery (process exit + re-read), corrupted file handling, missing directory creation, default state shape, and type validation\n50\t   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n51\t\n52\t## Tasks / Subtasks\n53\t\n54\t- [ ] Task 1: Define `WorkflowState` TypeScript interface (AC: #1, #2)\n55\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` with the `WorkflowState` interface\n56\t  - [ ] Define `TaskCheckpoint` sub-interface: `{ task_name: string; story_key: string; completed_at: string; session_id?: string }`\n57\t  - [ ] Define `EvaluatorScore` sub-interface: `{ iteration: number; passed: number; failed: number; unknown: number; total: number; timestamp: string }`\n58\t  - [ ] Define `CircuitBreakerState` sub-interface: `{ triggered: boolean; reason: string | null; score_history: number[] }`\n59\t  - [ ] Export all interfaces and types\n60\t\n61\t- [ ] Task 2: Implement `writeState()` (AC: #1, #5, #6)\n62\t  - [ ] Accept `WorkflowState` and optional `dir` parameter (defaults to `process.cwd()`)\n63\t  - [ ] Create `.codeharness/` directory with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })` if absent\n64\t  - [ ] Serialize state with `yaml` package `stringify()` — use `writeFileSync` for atomic-enough writes\n65\t  - [ ] Write to `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`\n66\t\n67\t- [ ] Task 3: Implement `readState()` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n68\t  - [ ] Accept optional `dir` parameter (defaults to `process.cwd()`)\n69\t  - [ ] If file does not exist, return `getDefaultWorkflowState()`\n70\t  - [ ] Parse YAML with `yaml` package `parse()`\n71\t  - [ ] Validate parsed object has required fields (basic shape check)\n72\t  - [ ] On parse error or invalid shape: `warn()` about corruption, return `getDefaultWorkflowState()`\n73\t\n74\t- [ ] Task 4: Implement `getDefaultWorkflowState()` (AC: #1, #4)\n75\t  - [ ] Return a `WorkflowState` with: `workflow_name: ''`, `started: ''`, `iteration: 0`, `phase: 'idle'`, `tasks_completed: []`, `evaluator_scores: []`, `circuit_breaker: { triggered: false, reason: null, score_history: [] }`\n76\t\n77\t- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #7)\n78\t  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts`\n79\t  - [ ] Test: write then read round-trip preserves all fields\n80\t  - [ ] Test: readState on non-existent file returns default state\n81\t  - [ ] Test: readState on corrupted YAML returns default state and warns\n82\t  - [ ] Test: readState on empty file returns default state\n83\t  - [ ] Test: readState on invalid shape (missing fields) returns default state\n84\t  - [ ] Test: writeState creates `.codeharness/` directory if missing\n85\t  - [ ] Test: writeState overwrites existing file completely\n86\t  - [ ] Test: default state has correct shape and field types\n87\t  - [ ] Test: state survives cross-\"process\" (write in one scope, read in another)\n88\t  - [ ] Target 80%+ coverage on workflow-state.ts\n89\t\n90\t## Dev Notes\n91\t\n92\t### This is a NEW module, not a refactor of state.ts\n93\t\n94\tThe existing `src/lib/state.ts` manages **harness configuration state** (stack detection, coverage settings, session flags) stored in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` as YAML frontmatter in markdown. That module is KEPT and untouched.\n95\t\n96\tThis new `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` manages **workflow execution state** (what task the engine last completed, evaluator scores, circuit breaker) stored in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` as plain YAML. Different file, different purpose, different interface.\n97\t\n98\tDo NOT modify, extend, or import from `src/lib/state.ts`. Do NOT merge these two state concepts.\n99\t\n100\t### Architecture Constraints\n101\t\n102\t- **Module location:** `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` with test at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts`\n103\t- **State file location:** `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — plain YAML, no markdown wrapper\n104\t- **Dependency:** `yaml` package (v2.8.2, already in package.json) for parse/stringify. `node:fs` and `node:path` for I/O.\n105\t- **No other dependencies.** This is the foundation module — it must not import from any other `src/lib/` module except `output.ts` for `warn()`.\n106\t- **Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions (`readState`, `writeState`, `getDefaultWorkflowState`), `PascalCase` for types (`WorkflowState`, `TaskCheckpoint`, `EvaluatorScore`, `CircuitBreakerState`)\n107\t- **File naming:** `kebab-case.ts` — already established pattern\n108\t\n109\t### State File Format\n110\t\n111\t```yaml\n112\t# .codeharness/workflow-state.yaml\n113\tworkflow_name: default\n114\tstarted: \"2026-04-02T14:30:00.000Z\"\n115\titeration: 2\n116\tphase: verify\n117\ttasks_completed:\n118\t  - task_name: implement\n119\t    story_key: 1-3-workflow-state-module\n120\t    completed_at: \"2026-04-02T14:31:00.000Z\"\n121\t    session_id: sess_abc123\n122\t  - task_name: verify\n123\t    story_key: 1-3-workflow-state-module\n124\t    completed_at: \"2026-04-02T14:35:00.000Z\"\n125\tevaluator_scores:\n126\t  - iteration: 1\n127\t    passed: 3\n128\t    failed: 1\n129\t    unknown: 0\n130\t    total: 4\n131\t    timestamp: \"2026-04-02T14:35:00.000Z\"\n132\tcircuit_breaker:\n133\t  triggered: false\n134\t  reason: null\n135\t  score_history:\n136\t    - 0.75\n137\t```\n138\t\n139\t### YAML Key Convention\n140\t\n141\tAll keys use `snake_case` per architecture-v2.md. The `yaml` package v2 handles this natively — no key transformation needed.\n142\t\n143\t### Error Handling\n144\t\n145\t| Failure | Response |\n146\t|---------|----------|\n147\t| File does not exist | Return default state (not an error — first run) |\n148\t| YAML parse error | Warn, return default state |\n149\t| Invalid shape (missing required fields) | Warn, return default state |\n150\t| Directory missing on write | Create with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })` |\n151\t| Write I/O error | Let it throw (caller handles — this is a fatal condition for the engine) |\n152\t\n153\t### What Downstream Modules Will Need\n154\t\n155\tThis module is the **first in the dependency chain** (architecture-v2.md AD1). Every subsequent module depends on it:\n156\t- `workflow-engine` (Epic 5) will call `writeState()` after every task completion\n157\t- `evaluator` (Epic 6) will read scores from state\n158\t- `circuit-breaker` (Epic 7) will read `score_history` from state\n159\t- `status` command (Epic 5) will call `readState()` to display progress\n160\t\n161\tDesign the interface to be stable. The `WorkflowState` type will be imported by 4+ modules.\n162\t\n163\t### Previous Story Intelligence\n164\t\n165\tStory 1.2 deleted `src/lib/state.ts`'s legacy companions (patch-engine, retry-state, verifier-session) but kept `state.ts` itself. Recent commits show clean deletion patterns — remove files, remove imports, fix tests. No surprises.\n166\t\n167\tThe `warn()` function from `src/lib/output.ts` is the established pattern for non-fatal warnings (used in state.ts recovery). Use the same pattern here.\n168\t\n169\t### Git Intelligence\n170\t\n171\tRecent commit `e3f4129` deleted ralph loop and legacy verification. The codebase is now clean of legacy dependencies. The `yaml` package import pattern is established in `src/lib/state.ts` — use `import { parse, stringify } from 'yaml'`.\n172\t\n173\tThe `node:fs` import pattern uses named imports: `import { existsSync, mkdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs'`.\n174\t\n175\t### Testing Standards\n176\t\n177\t- Framework: vitest (v4.1.0)\n178\t- Pattern: `describe`/`it`/`expect` with `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for temp directory setup/teardown\n179\t- Temp directories: `mkdtempSync(join(tmpdir(), 'ch-wfstate-test-'))` — see `state.test.ts` for established pattern\n180\t- Coverage target: 80%+ on `workflow-state.ts`\n181\t- Mock only `warn()` from output.ts — everything else uses real file I/O in temp directories\n182\t\n183\t### Project Structure Notes\n184\t\n185\t- File lives at `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — same directory as other core modules\n186\t- Test at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts` — co-located test pattern\n187\t- State file at `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — NOT in `.claude/` (that's for harness config state)\n188\t- No changes to `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, or build config needed\n189\t\n190\t### References\n191\t\n192\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 1.3: Workflow State Module]\n193\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — workflow-state]\n194\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n195\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries]\n196\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Error Handling Patterns]\n197\t- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR6, NFR8]\n198\t\n199\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n200\t## Verification Requirements\n201\t\n202\t- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/1-3-workflow-state-module-proof.md)\n203\t- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n204\t- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n205\t\n206\t## Documentation Requirements\n207\t\n208\t- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n209\t- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/1-3-workflow-state-module.md\n210\t\n211\t## Testing Requirements\n212\t\n213\t- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n214\t- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n215\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n216\t\n217\t## Dev Agent Record\n218\t\n219\t### Agent Model Used\n220\t\n221\t### Debug Log References\n222\t\n223\t### Completion Notes List\n224\t\n225\t### File List\n226\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aeb5b1ee-06a7-4bdc-8279-6cd22d306d14","uuid":"0f47ed5c-ef8a-425d-846d-331f6883cd25","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:45:42.711Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/1-3-workflow-state-module.md","content":"# Story 1.3: Workflow State Module\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want a workflow-state module that persists execution state to YAML,\nso that the engine can resume from the last completed task after a crash.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. **Given** no `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` exists\n   **When** `writeState()` is called after a task completion\n   **Then** `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` is created with all required fields: `workflow_name` (string), `started` (ISO timestamp), `iteration` (number), `phase` (string), `tasks_completed` (array of task checkpoint objects), `evaluator_scores` (array of score objects), and `circuit_breaker` (object with `triggered`, `reason`, `score_history`)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n2. **Given** a valid `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` exists on disk\n   **When** `readState()` is called\n   **Then** the returned object matches the `WorkflowState` TypeScript interface with all fields correctly typed\n   **And** round-trip fidelity is preserved: `readState(writeState(state))` returns an equivalent object\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n3. **Given** a workflow-state.yaml was written by a previous process\n   **When** the process exits and a new process calls `readState()`\n   **Then** the previously written state is returned intact (state survives process exit)\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n4. **Given** a corrupted or invalid YAML file at `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`\n   **When** `readState()` is called\n   **Then** it returns a default empty state (not throw) so the engine can start fresh\n   **And** the corrupted file is not silently ignored — a warning is emitted via the `warn()` output utility\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n5. **Given** the `.codeharness/` directory does not exist\n   **When** `writeState()` is called\n   **Then** the directory is created automatically before writing the file\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n6. **Given** concurrent or rapid sequential `writeState()` calls\n   **When** each call provides a different state\n   **Then** the file always contains a complete, valid YAML document (no partial writes)\n   **And** the last write wins\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n7. **Given** the workflow-state module source file\n   **When** unit tests are run via `npm run test:unit`\n   **Then** all tests pass with 80%+ code coverage on `src/lib/workflow-state.ts`\n   **And** tests cover: read, write, crash recovery (process exit + re-read), corrupted file handling, missing directory creation, default state shape, and type validation\n   <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Define `WorkflowState` TypeScript interface (AC: #1, #2)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` with the `WorkflowState` interface\n  - [ ] Define `TaskCheckpoint` sub-interface: `{ task_name: string; story_key: string; completed_at: string; session_id?: string }`\n  - [ ] Define `EvaluatorScore` sub-interface: `{ iteration: number; passed: number; failed: number; unknown: number; total: number; timestamp: string }`\n  - [ ] Define `CircuitBreakerState` sub-interface: `{ triggered: boolean; reason: string | null; score_history: number[] }`\n  - [ ] Export all interfaces and types\n\n- [ ] Task 2: Implement `writeState()` (AC: #1, #5, #6)\n  - [ ] Accept `WorkflowState` and optional `dir` parameter (defaults to `process.cwd()`)\n  - [ ] Create `.codeharness/` directory with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })` if absent\n  - [ ] Serialize state with `yaml` package `stringify()` — use `writeFileSync` for atomic-enough writes\n  - [ ] Write to `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml`\n\n- [ ] Task 3: Implement `readState()` (AC: #2, #3, #4)\n  - [ ] Accept optional `dir` parameter (defaults to `process.cwd()`)\n  - [ ] If file does not exist, return `getDefaultWorkflowState()`\n  - [ ] Parse YAML with `yaml` package `parse()`\n  - [ ] Validate parsed object has required fields (basic shape check)\n  - [ ] On parse error or invalid shape: `warn()` about corruption, return `getDefaultWorkflowState()`\n\n- [ ] Task 4: Implement `getDefaultWorkflowState()` (AC: #1, #4)\n  - [ ] Return a `WorkflowState` with: `workflow_name: ''`, `started: ''`, `iteration: 0`, `phase: 'idle'`, `tasks_completed: []`, `evaluator_scores: []`, `circuit_breaker: { triggered: false, reason: null, score_history: [] }`\n\n- [ ] Task 5: Write unit tests (AC: #7)\n  - [ ] Create `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts`\n  - [ ] Test: write then read round-trip preserves all fields\n  - [ ] Test: readState on non-existent file returns default state\n  - [ ] Test: readState on corrupted YAML returns default state and warns\n  - [ ] Test: readState on empty file returns default state\n  - [ ] Test: readState on invalid shape (missing fields) returns default state\n  - [ ] Test: writeState creates `.codeharness/` directory if missing\n  - [ ] Test: writeState overwrites existing file completely\n  - [ ] Test: default state has correct shape and field types\n  - [ ] Test: state survives cross-\"process\" (write in one scope, read in another)\n  - [ ] Target 80%+ coverage on workflow-state.ts\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### This is a NEW module, not a refactor of state.ts\n\nThe existing `src/lib/state.ts` manages **harness configuration state** (stack detection, coverage settings, session flags) stored in `.claude/codeharness.local.md` as YAML frontmatter in markdown. That module is KEPT and untouched.\n\nThis new `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` manages **workflow execution state** (what task the engine last completed, evaluator scores, circuit breaker) stored in `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` as plain YAML. Different file, different purpose, different interface.\n\nDo NOT modify, extend, or import from `src/lib/state.ts`. Do NOT merge these two state concepts.\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **Module location:** `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` with test at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts`\n- **State file location:** `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — plain YAML, no markdown wrapper\n- **Dependency:** `yaml` package (v2.8.2, already in package.json) for parse/stringify. `node:fs` and `node:path` for I/O.\n- **No other dependencies.** This is the foundation module — it must not import from any other `src/lib/` module except `output.ts` for `warn()`.\n- **Export naming:** `camelCase` for functions (`readState`, `writeState`, `getDefaultWorkflowState`), `PascalCase` for types (`WorkflowState`, `TaskCheckpoint`, `EvaluatorScore`, `CircuitBreakerState`)\n- **File naming:** `kebab-case.ts` — already established pattern\n\n### State File Format\n\n```yaml\n# .codeharness/workflow-state.yaml\nworkflow_name: default\nstarted: \"2026-04-02T14:30:00.000Z\"\niteration: 2\nphase: verify\ntasks_completed:\n  - task_name: implement\n    story_key: 1-3-workflow-state-module\n    completed_at: \"2026-04-02T14:31:00.000Z\"\n    session_id: sess_abc123\n  - task_name: verify\n    story_key: 1-3-workflow-state-module\n    completed_at: \"2026-04-02T14:35:00.000Z\"\nevaluator_scores:\n  - iteration: 1\n    passed: 3\n    failed: 1\n    unknown: 0\n    total: 4\n    timestamp: \"2026-04-02T14:35:00.000Z\"\ncircuit_breaker:\n  triggered: false\n  reason: null\n  score_history:\n    - 0.75\n```\n\n### YAML Key Convention\n\nAll keys use `snake_case` per architecture-v2.md. The `yaml` package v2 handles this natively — no key transformation needed.\n\n### Error Handling\n\n| Failure | Response |\n|---------|----------|\n| File does not exist | Return default state (not an error — first run) |\n| YAML parse error | Warn, return default state |\n| Invalid shape (missing required fields) | Warn, return default state |\n| Directory missing on write | Create with `mkdirSync({ recursive: true })` |\n| Write I/O error | Let it throw (caller handles — this is a fatal condition for the engine) |\n\n### What Downstream Modules Will Need\n\nThis module is the **first in the dependency chain** (architecture-v2.md AD1). Every subsequent module depends on it:\n- `workflow-engine` (Epic 5) will call `writeState()` after every task completion\n- `evaluator` (Epic 6) will read scores from state\n- `circuit-breaker` (Epic 7) will read `score_history` from state\n- `status` command (Epic 5) will call `readState()` to display progress\n\nDesign the interface to be stable. The `WorkflowState` type will be imported by 4+ modules.\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence\n\nStory 1.2 deleted `src/lib/state.ts`'s legacy companions (patch-engine, retry-state, verifier-session) but kept `state.ts` itself. Recent commits show clean deletion patterns — remove files, remove imports, fix tests. No surprises.\n\nThe `warn()` function from `src/lib/output.ts` is the established pattern for non-fatal warnings (used in state.ts recovery). Use the same pattern here.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commit `e3f4129` deleted ralph loop and legacy verification. The codebase is now clean of legacy dependencies. The `yaml` package import pattern is established in `src/lib/state.ts` — use `import { parse, stringify } from 'yaml'`.\n\nThe `node:fs` import pattern uses named imports: `import { existsSync, mkdirSync, readFileSync, writeFileSync } from 'node:fs'`.\n\n### Testing Standards\n\n- Framework: vitest (v4.1.0)\n- Pattern: `describe`/`it`/`expect` with `beforeEach`/`afterEach` for temp directory setup/teardown\n- Temp directories: `mkdtempSync(join(tmpdir(), 'ch-wfstate-test-'))` — see `state.test.ts` for established pattern\n- Coverage target: 80%+ on `workflow-state.ts`\n- Mock only `warn()` from output.ts — everything else uses real file I/O in temp directories\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- File lives at `src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — same directory as other core modules\n- Test at `src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts` — co-located test pattern\n- State file at `.codeharness/workflow-state.yaml` — NOT in `.claude/` (that's for harness config state)\n- No changes to `package.json`, `tsconfig.json`, or build config needed\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-v2.md#Story 1.3: Workflow State Module]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#AD1: Module Boundaries — workflow-state]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Implementation Patterns & Consistency Rules]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Project Structure & Boundaries]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-v2.md#Error Handling Patterns]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/prd-evaluator-redesign.md#NFR6, NFR8]\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (verification/1-3-workflow-state-module-proof.md)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence via docker exec\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (80%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in docs/exec-plans/active/1-3-workflow-state-module.md\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Coverage target: 80%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n","numLines":226,"startLine":1,"totalLines":226}}}
