{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UxMjpkUMJk1JZMdcnHpbSq","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t---\n2\ttitle: 'Enhanced Dev Story Definition of Done Checklist'\n3\tvalidation-target: 'Story markdown ({{story_path}})'\n4\tvalidation-criticality: 'HIGHEST'\n5\trequired-inputs:\n6\t  - 'Story markdown file with enhanced Dev Notes containing comprehensive implementation context'\n7\t  - 'Completed Tasks/Subtasks section with all items marked [x]'\n8\t  - 'Updated File List section with all changed files'\n9\t  - 'Updated Dev Agent Record with implementation notes'\n10\toptional-inputs:\n11\t  - 'Test results output'\n12\t  - 'CI logs'\n13\t  - 'Linting reports'\n14\tvalidation-rules:\n15\t  - 'Only permitted story sections modified: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status'\n16\t  - 'All implementation requirements from story Dev Notes must be satisfied'\n17\t  - 'Definition of Done checklist must pass completely'\n18\t  - 'Enhanced story context must contain sufficient technical guidance'\n19\t---\n20\t\n21\t# 🎯 Enhanced Definition of Done Checklist\n22\t\n23\t**Critical validation:** Story is truly ready for review only when ALL items below are satisfied\n24\t\n25\t## 📋 Context & Requirements Validation\n26\t\n27\t- [ ] **Story Context Completeness:** Dev Notes contains ALL necessary technical requirements, architecture patterns, and implementation guidance\n28\t- [ ] **Architecture Compliance:** Implementation follows all architectural requirements specified in Dev Notes\n29\t- [ ] **Technical Specifications:** All technical specifications (libraries, frameworks, versions) from Dev Notes are implemented correctly\n30\t- [ ] **Previous Story Learnings:** Previous story insights incorporated (if applicable) and build upon appropriately\n31\t\n32\t## ✅ Implementation Completion\n33\t\n34\t- [ ] **All Tasks Complete:** Every task and subtask marked complete with [x]\n35\t- [ ] **Acceptance Criteria Satisfaction:** Implementation satisfies EVERY Acceptance Criterion in the story\n36\t- [ ] **No Ambiguous Implementation:** Clear, unambiguous implementation that meets story requirements\n37\t- [ ] **Edge Cases Handled:** Error conditions and edge cases appropriately addressed\n38\t- [ ] **Dependencies Within Scope:** Only uses dependencies specified in story or project-context.md\n39\t\n40\t## 🧪 Testing & Quality Assurance\n41\t\n42\t- [ ] **Unit Tests:** Unit tests added/updated for ALL core functionality introduced/changed by this story\n43\t- [ ] **Integration Tests:** Integration tests added/updated for component interactions when story requirements demand them\n44\t- [ ] **End-to-End Tests:** End-to-end tests created for critical user flows when story requirements specify them\n45\t- [ ] **Test Coverage:** Tests cover acceptance criteria and edge cases from story Dev Notes\n46\t- [ ] **Regression Prevention:** ALL existing tests pass (no regressions introduced)\n47\t- [ ] **Code Quality:** Linting and static checks pass when configured in project\n48\t- [ ] **Test Framework Compliance:** Tests use project's testing frameworks and patterns from Dev Notes\n49\t\n50\t## 📝 Documentation & Tracking\n51\t\n52\t- [ ] **File List Complete:** File List includes EVERY new, modified, or deleted file (paths relative to repo root)\n53\t- [ ] **Dev Agent Record Updated:** Contains relevant Implementation Notes and/or Debug Log for this work\n54\t- [ ] **Change Log Updated:** Change Log includes clear summary of what changed and why\n55\t- [ ] **Review Follow-ups:** All review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) completed and corresponding review items marked resolved (if applicable)\n56\t- [ ] **Story Structure Compliance:** Only permitted sections of story file were modified\n57\t\n58\t## 🔚 Final Status Verification\n59\t\n60\t- [ ] **Story Status Updated:** Story Status set to \"review\"\n61\t- [ ] **Sprint Status Updated:** Sprint status updated to \"review\" (when sprint tracking is used)\n62\t- [ ] **Quality Gates Passed:** All quality checks and validations completed successfully\n63\t- [ ] **No HALT Conditions:** No blocking issues or incomplete work remaining\n64\t- [ ] **User Communication Ready:** Implementation summary prepared for user review\n65\t\n66\t## 🎯 Final Validation Output\n67\t\n68\t```\n69\tDefinition of Done: {{PASS/FAIL}}\n70\t\n71\t✅ **Story Ready for Review:** {{story_key}}\n72\t📊 **Completion Score:** {{completed_items}}/{{total_items}} items passed\n73\t🔍 **Quality Gates:** {{quality_gates_status}}\n74\t📋 **Test Results:** {{test_results_summary}}\n75\t📝 **Documentation:** {{documentation_status}}\n76\t```\n77\t\n78\t**If FAIL:** List specific failures and required actions before story can be marked Ready for Review\n79\t\n80\t**If PASS:** Story is fully ready for code review and production consideration\n81\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HNbP4Hg5VKRrkree5HJepQ","session_id":"aeb5b1ee-06a7-4bdc-8279-6cd22d306d14","uuid":"7d8e1150-1786-4682-95de-ffa0f05af4d8","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:46:15.391Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01APaKEukh3EnNPMkN6qbesA","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t<workflow>\n2\t  <critical>The workflow execution engine is governed by: {project-root}/_bmad/core/tasks/workflow.xml</critical>\n3\t  <critical>You MUST have already loaded and processed: {installed_path}/workflow.yaml</critical>\n4\t  <critical>Communicate all responses in {communication_language} and language MUST be tailored to {user_skill_level}</critical>\n5\t  <critical>Generate all documents in {document_output_language}</critical>\n6\t  <critical>Only modify the story file in these areas: Tasks/Subtasks checkboxes, Dev Agent Record (Debug Log, Completion Notes), File List,\n7\t    Change Log, and Status</critical>\n8\t  <critical>Execute ALL steps in exact order; do NOT skip steps</critical>\n9\t  <critical>Absolutely DO NOT stop because of \"milestones\", \"significant progress\", or \"session boundaries\". Continue in a single execution\n10\t    until the story is COMPLETE (all ACs satisfied and all tasks/subtasks checked) UNLESS a HALT condition is triggered or the USER gives\n11\t    other instruction.</critical>\n12\t  <critical>Do NOT schedule a \"next session\" or request review pauses unless a HALT condition applies. Only Step 6 decides completion.</critical>\n13\t  <critical>User skill level ({user_skill_level}) affects conversation style ONLY, not code updates.</critical>\n14\t\n15\t  <step n=\"1\" goal=\"Find next ready story and load it\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n16\t    <check if=\"{{story_path}} is provided\">\n17\t      <action>Use {{story_path}} directly</action>\n18\t      <action>Read COMPLETE story file</action>\n19\t      <action>Extract story_key from filename or metadata</action>\n20\t      <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n21\t    </check>\n22\t\n23\t    <!-- Sprint-based story discovery -->\n24\t    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n25\t      <critical>MUST read COMPLETE sprint-status.yaml file from start to end to preserve order</critical>\n26\t      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n27\t      <action>Read ALL lines from beginning to end - do not skip any content</action>\n28\t      <action>Parse the development_status section completely to understand story order</action>\n29\t\n30\t      <action>Find the FIRST story (by reading in order from top to bottom) where:\n31\t        - Key matches pattern: number-number-name (e.g., \"1-2-user-auth\")\n32\t        - NOT an epic key (epic-X) or retrospective (epic-X-retrospective)\n33\t        - Status value equals \"ready-for-dev\"\n34\t      </action>\n35\t\n36\t      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev or in-progress story found\">\n37\t        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found in sprint-status.yaml\n38\t\n39\t          **Current Sprint Status:** {{sprint_status_summary}}\n40\t\n41\t          **What would you like to do?**\n42\t          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n43\t          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories before development (recommended quality check)\n44\t          3. Specify a particular story file to develop (provide full path)\n45\t          4. Check {{sprint_status}} file to see current sprint status\n46\t\n47\t          💡 **Tip:** Stories in `ready-for-dev` may not have been validated. Consider running `validate-create-story` first for a quality\n48\t          check.\n49\t        </output>\n50\t        <ask>Choose option [1], [2], [3], or [4], or specify story file path:</ask>\n51\t\n52\t        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n53\t          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n54\t        </check>\n55\t\n56\t        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n57\t          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n58\t        </check>\n59\t\n60\t        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n61\t          <ask>Provide the story file path to develop:</ask>\n62\t          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n63\t          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n64\t        </check>\n65\t\n66\t        <check if=\"user chooses '4'\">\n67\t          <output>Loading {{sprint_status}} for detailed status review...</output>\n68\t          <action>Display detailed sprint status analysis</action>\n69\t          <action>HALT - User can review sprint status and provide story path</action>\n70\t        </check>\n71\t\n72\t        <check if=\"user provides story file path\">\n73\t          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n74\t          <goto anchor=\"task_check\" />\n75\t        </check>\n76\t      </check>\n77\t    </check>\n78\t\n79\t    <!-- Non-sprint story discovery -->\n80\t    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n81\t      <action>Search {implementation_artifacts} for stories directly</action>\n82\t      <action>Find stories with \"ready-for-dev\" status in files</action>\n83\t      <action>Look for story files matching pattern: *-*-*.md</action>\n84\t      <action>Read each candidate story file to check Status section</action>\n85\t\n86\t      <check if=\"no ready-for-dev stories found in story files\">\n87\t        <output>📋 No ready-for-dev stories found\n88\t\n89\t          **Available Options:**\n90\t          1. Run `create-story` to create next story from epics with comprehensive context\n91\t          2. Run `*validate-create-story` to improve existing stories\n92\t          3. Specify which story to develop\n93\t        </output>\n94\t        <ask>What would you like to do? Choose option [1], [2], or [3]:</ask>\n95\t\n96\t        <check if=\"user chooses '1'\">\n97\t          <action>HALT - Run create-story to create next story</action>\n98\t        </check>\n99\t\n100\t        <check if=\"user chooses '2'\">\n101\t          <action>HALT - Run validate-create-story to improve existing stories</action>\n102\t        </check>\n103\t\n104\t        <check if=\"user chooses '3'\">\n105\t          <ask>It's unclear what story you want developed. Please provide the full path to the story file:</ask>\n106\t          <action>Store user-provided story path as {{story_path}}</action>\n107\t          <action>Continue with provided story file</action>\n108\t        </check>\n109\t      </check>\n110\t\n111\t      <check if=\"ready-for-dev story found in files\">\n112\t        <action>Use discovered story file and extract story_key</action>\n113\t      </check>\n114\t    </check>\n115\t\n116\t    <action>Store the found story_key (e.g., \"1-2-user-authentication\") for later status updates</action>\n117\t    <action>Find matching story file in {implementation_artifacts} using story_key pattern: {{story_key}}.md</action>\n118\t    <action>Read COMPLETE story file from discovered path</action>\n119\t\n120\t    <anchor id=\"task_check\" />\n121\t\n122\t    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n123\t\n124\t    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n125\t    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n126\t    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n127\t\n128\t    <action>Identify first incomplete task (unchecked [ ]) in Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n129\t\n130\t    <action if=\"no incomplete tasks\">\n131\t      <goto step=\"6\">Completion sequence</goto>\n132\t    </action>\n133\t    <action if=\"story file inaccessible\">HALT: \"Cannot develop story without access to story file\"</action>\n134\t    <action if=\"incomplete task or subtask requirements ambiguous\">ASK user to clarify or HALT</action>\n135\t  </step>\n136\t\n137\t  <step n=\"2\" goal=\"Load project context and story information\">\n138\t    <critical>Load all available context to inform implementation</critical>\n139\t\n140\t    <action>Load {project_context} for coding standards and project-wide patterns (if exists)</action>\n141\t    <action>Parse sections: Story, Acceptance Criteria, Tasks/Subtasks, Dev Notes, Dev Agent Record, File List, Change Log, Status</action>\n142\t    <action>Load comprehensive context from story file's Dev Notes section</action>\n143\t    <action>Extract developer guidance from Dev Notes: architecture requirements, previous learnings, technical specifications</action>\n144\t    <action>Use enhanced story context to inform implementation decisions and approaches</action>\n145\t    <output>✅ **Context Loaded**\n146\t      Story and project context available for implementation\n147\t    </output>\n148\t  </step>\n149\t\n150\t  <step n=\"3\" goal=\"Detect review continuation and extract review context\">\n151\t    <critical>Determine if this is a fresh start or continuation after code review</critical>\n152\t\n153\t    <action>Check if \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section exists in the story file</action>\n154\t    <action>Check if \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection exists under Tasks/Subtasks</action>\n155\t\n156\t    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section exists\">\n157\t      <action>Set review_continuation = true</action>\n158\t      <action>Extract from \"Senior Developer Review (AI)\" section:\n159\t        - Review outcome (Approve/Changes Requested/Blocked)\n160\t        - Review date\n161\t        - Total action items with checkboxes (count checked vs unchecked)\n162\t        - Severity breakdown (High/Med/Low counts)\n163\t      </action>\n164\t      <action>Count unchecked [ ] review follow-up tasks in \"Review Follow-ups (AI)\" subsection</action>\n165\t      <action>Store list of unchecked review items as {{pending_review_items}}</action>\n166\t\n167\t      <output>⏯️ **Resuming Story After Code Review** ({{review_date}})\n168\t\n169\t        **Review Outcome:** {{review_outcome}}\n170\t        **Action Items:** {{unchecked_review_count}} remaining to address\n171\t        **Priorities:** {{high_count}} High, {{med_count}} Medium, {{low_count}} Low\n172\t\n173\t        **Strategy:** Will prioritize review follow-up tasks (marked [AI-Review]) before continuing with regular tasks.\n174\t      </output>\n175\t    </check>\n176\t\n177\t    <check if=\"Senior Developer Review section does NOT exist\">\n178\t      <action>Set review_continuation = false</action>\n179\t      <action>Set {{pending_review_items}} = empty</action>\n180\t\n181\t      <output>🚀 **Starting Fresh Implementation**\n182\t\n183\t        Story: {{story_key}}\n184\t        Story Status: {{current_status}}\n185\t        First incomplete task: {{first_task_description}}\n186\t      </output>\n187\t    </check>\n188\t  </step>\n189\t\n190\t  <step n=\"4\" goal=\"Mark story in-progress\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n191\t    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file exists\">\n192\t      <action>Load the FULL file: {{sprint_status}}</action>\n193\t      <action>Read all development_status entries to find {{story_key}}</action>\n194\t      <action>Get current status value for development_status[{{story_key}}]</action>\n195\t\n196\t      <check if=\"current status == 'ready-for-dev' OR review_continuation == true\">\n197\t        <action>Update the story in the sprint status report to = \"in-progress\"</action>\n198\t        <output>🚀 Starting work on story {{story_key}}\n199\t          Status updated: ready-for-dev → in-progress\n200\t        </output>\n201\t      </check>\n202\t\n203\t      <check if=\"current status == 'in-progress'\">\n204\t        <output>⏯️ Resuming work on story {{story_key}}\n205\t          Story is already marked in-progress\n206\t        </output>\n207\t      </check>\n208\t\n209\t      <check if=\"current status is neither ready-for-dev nor in-progress\">\n210\t        <output>⚠️ Unexpected story status: {{current_status}}\n211\t          Expected ready-for-dev or in-progress. Continuing anyway...\n212\t        </output>\n213\t      </check>\n214\t\n215\t      <action>Store {{current_sprint_status}} for later use</action>\n216\t    </check>\n217\t\n218\t    <check if=\"{{sprint_status}} file does NOT exist\">\n219\t      <output>ℹ️ No sprint status file exists - story progress will be tracked in story file only</output>\n220\t      <action>Set {{current_sprint_status}} = \"no-sprint-tracking\"</action>\n221\t    </check>\n222\t  </step>\n223\t\n224\t  <step n=\"5\" goal=\"Implement task following red-green-refactor cycle\">\n225\t    <critical>FOLLOW THE STORY FILE TASKS/SUBTASKS SEQUENCE EXACTLY AS WRITTEN - NO DEVIATION</critical>\n226\t\n227\t    <action>Review the current task/subtask from the story file - this is your authoritative implementation guide</action>\n228\t    <action>Plan implementation following red-green-refactor cycle</action>\n229\t\n230\t    <!-- RED PHASE -->\n231\t    <action>Write FAILING tests first for the task/subtask functionality</action>\n232\t    <action>Confirm tests fail before implementation - this validates test correctness</action>\n233\t\n234\t    <!-- GREEN PHASE -->\n235\t    <action>Implement MINIMAL code to make tests pass</action>\n236\t    <action>Run tests to confirm they now pass</action>\n237\t    <action>Handle error conditions and edge cases as specified in task/subtask</action>\n238\t\n239\t    <!-- REFACTOR PHASE -->\n240\t    <action>Improve code structure while keeping tests green</action>\n241\t    <action>Ensure code follows architecture patterns and coding standards from Dev Notes</action>\n242\t\n243\t    <action>Document technical approach and decisions in Dev Agent Record → Implementation Plan</action>\n244\t\n245\t    <action if=\"new dependencies required beyond story specifications\">HALT: \"Additional dependencies need user approval\"</action>\n246\t    <action if=\"3 consecutive implementation failures occur\">HALT and request guidance</action>\n247\t    <action if=\"required configuration is missing\">HALT: \"Cannot proceed without necessary configuration files\"</action>\n248\t\n249\t    <critical>NEVER implement anything not mapped to a specific task/subtask in the story file</critical>\n250\t    <critical>NEVER proceed to next task until current task/subtask is complete AND tests pass</critical>\n251\t    <critical>Execute continuously without pausing until all tasks/subtasks are complete or explicit HALT condition</critical>\n252\t    <critical>Do NOT propose to pause for review until Step 9 completion gates are satisfied</critical>\n253\t  </step>\n254\t\n255\t  <!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:dev-enforcement -->\n256\t## Codeharness Enforcement\n257\t\n258\t### Observability Check\n259\t- [ ] Query VictoriaLogs after test runs to verify telemetry flows\n260\t\n261\t### Documentation Update\n262\t- [ ] AGENTS.md updated for all changed modules\n263\t\n264\t### Test Enforcement\n265\t- [ ] All tests pass\n266\t- [ ] Coverage gate: 100% of new/changed code\n267\t<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:dev-enforcement -->\n268\t\n269\t  <step n=\"6\" goal=\"Author comprehensive tests\">\n270\t    <action>Create unit tests for business logic and core functionality introduced/changed by the task</action>\n271\t    <action>Add integration tests for component interactions specified in story requirements</action>\n272\t    <action>Include end-to-end tests for critical user flows when story requirements demand them</action>\n273\t    <action>Cover edge cases and error handling scenarios identified in story Dev Notes</action>\n274\t  </step>\n275\t\n276\t  <step n=\"7\" goal=\"Run validations and tests\">\n277\t    <action>Determine how to run tests for this repo (infer test framework from project structure)</action>\n278\t    <action>Run all existing tests to ensure no regressions</action>\n279\t    <action>Run the new tests to verify implementation correctness</action>\n280\t    <action>Run linting and code quality checks if configured in project</action>\n281\t    <action>Validate implementation meets ALL story acceptance criteria; enforce quantitative thresholds explicitly</action>\n282\t    <action if=\"regression tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - identify breaking changes immediately</action>\n283\t    <action if=\"new tests fail\">STOP and fix before continuing - ensure implementation correctness</action>\n284\t  </step>\n285\t\n286\t  <step n=\"8\" goal=\"Validate and mark task complete ONLY when fully done\">\n287\t    <critical>NEVER mark a task complete unless ALL conditions are met - NO LYING OR CHEATING</critical>\n288\t\n289\t    <!-- VALIDATION GATES -->\n290\t    <action>Verify ALL tests for this task/subtask ACTUALLY EXIST and PASS 100%</action>\n291\t    <action>Confirm implementation matches EXACTLY what the task/subtask specifies - no extra features</action>\n292\t    <action>Validate that ALL acceptance criteria related to this task are satisfied</action>\n293\t    <action>Run full test suite to ensure NO regressions introduced</action>\n294\t\n295\t    <!-- REVIEW FOLLOW-UP HANDLING -->\n296\t    <check if=\"task is review follow-up (has [AI-Review] prefix)\">\n297\t      <action>Extract review item details (severity, description, related AC/file)</action>\n298\t      <action>Add to resolution tracking list: {{resolved_review_items}}</action>\n299\t\n300\t      <!-- Mark task in Review Follow-ups section -->\n301\t      <action>Mark task checkbox [x] in \"Tasks/Subtasks → Review Follow-ups (AI)\" section</action>\n302\t\n303\t      <!-- CRITICAL: Also mark corresponding action item in review section -->\n304\t      <action>Find matching action item in \"Senior Developer Review (AI) → Action Items\" section by matching description</action>\n305\t      <action>Mark that action item checkbox [x] as resolved</action>\n306\t\n307\t      <action>Add to Dev Agent Record → Completion Notes: \"✅ Resolved review finding [{{severity}}]: {{description}}\"</action>\n308\t    </check>\n309\t\n310\t    <!-- ONLY MARK COMPLETE IF ALL VALIDATION PASS -->\n311\t    <check if=\"ALL validation gates pass AND tests ACTUALLY exist and pass\">\n312\t      <action>ONLY THEN mark the task (and subtasks) checkbox with [x]</action>\n313\t      <action>Update File List section with ALL new, modified, or deleted files (paths relative to repo root)</action>\n314\t      <action>Add completion notes to Dev Agent Record summarizing what was ACTUALLY implemented and tested</action>\n315\t    </check>\n316\t\n317\t    <check if=\"ANY validation fails\">\n318\t      <action>DO NOT mark task complete - fix issues first</action>\n319\t      <action>HALT if unable to fix validation failures</action>\n320\t    </check>\n321\t\n322\t    <check if=\"review_continuation == true and {{resolved_review_items}} is not empty\">\n323\t      <action>Count total resolved review items in this session</action>\n324\t      <action>Add Change Log entry: \"Addressed code review findings - {{resolved_count}} items resolved (Date: {{date}})\"</action>\n325\t    </check>\n326\t\n327\t    <action>Save the story file</action>\n328\t    <action>Determine if more incomplete tasks remain</action>\n329\t    <action if=\"more tasks remain\">\n330\t      <goto step=\"5\">Next task</goto>\n331\t    </action>\n332\t    <action if=\"no tasks remain\">\n333\t      <goto step=\"9\">Completion</goto>\n334\t    </action>\n335\t  </step>\n336\t\n337\t  <step n=\"9\" goal=\"Story completion and mark for review\" tag=\"sprint-status\">\n338\t    <action>Verify ALL tasks and subtasks are marked [x] (re-scan the story document now)</action>\n339\t    <action>Run the full regression suite (do not skip)</action>\n340\t    <action>Confirm File List includes every changed file</action>\n341\t    <action>Execute enhanced definition-of-done validation</action>\n342\t    <action>Update the story Status to: \"review\"</action>\n343\t\n344\t    <!-- Enhanced Definition of Done Validation -->\n345\t    <action>Validate definition-of-done checklist with essential requirements:\n346\t      - All tasks/subtasks marked complete with [x]\n347\t      - Implementation satisfies every Acceptance Criterion\n348\t      - Unit tests for core functionality added/updated\n349\t      - Integration tests for component interactions added when required\n350\t      - End-to-end tests for critical flows added when story demands them\n351\t      - All tests pass (no regressions, new tests successful)\n352\t      - Code quality checks pass (linting, static analysis if configured)\n353\t      - File List includes every new/modified/deleted file (relative paths)\n354\t      - Dev Agent Record contains implementation notes\n355\t      - Change Log includes summary of changes\n356\t      - Only permitted story sections were modified\n357\t    </action>\n358\t\n359\t    <!-- Mark story ready for review - sprint status conditional -->\n360\t    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists AND {{current_sprint_status}} != 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n361\t      <action>Load the FULL file: {sprint_status}</action>\n362\t      <action>Find development_status key matching {{story_key}}</action>\n363\t      <action>Verify current status is \"in-progress\" (expected previous state)</action>\n364\t      <action>Update development_status[{{story_key}}] = \"review\"</action>\n365\t      <action>Save file, preserving ALL comments and structure including STATUS DEFINITIONS</action>\n366\t      <output>✅ Story status updated to \"review\" in sprint-status.yaml</output>\n367\t    </check>\n368\t\n369\t    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file does NOT exist OR {{current_sprint_status}} == 'no-sprint-tracking'\">\n370\t      <output>ℹ️ Story status updated to \"review\" in story file (no sprint tracking configured)</output>\n371\t    </check>\n372\t\n373\t    <check if=\"story key not found in sprint status\">\n374\t      <output>⚠️ Story file updated, but sprint-status update failed: {{story_key}} not found\n375\t\n376\t        Story status is set to \"review\" in file, but sprint-status.yaml may be out of sync.\n377\t      </output>\n378\t    </check>\n379\t\n380\t    <!-- Final validation gates -->\n381\t    <action if=\"any task is incomplete\">HALT - Complete remaining tasks before marking ready for review</action>\n382\t    <action if=\"regression failures exist\">HALT - Fix regression issues before completing</action>\n383\t    <action if=\"File List is incomplete\">HALT - Update File List with all changed files</action>\n384\t    <action if=\"definition-of-done validation fails\">HALT - Address DoD failures before completing</action>\n385\t  </step>\n386\t\n387\t  <step n=\"10\" goal=\"Completion communication and user support\">\n388\t    <action>Execute the enhanced definition-of-done checklist using the validation framework</action>\n389\t    <action>Prepare a concise summary in Dev Agent Record → Completion Notes</action>\n390\t\n391\t    <action>Communicate to {user_name} that story implementation is complete and ready for review</action>\n392\t    <action>Summarize key accomplishments: story ID, story key, title, key changes made, tests added, files modified</action>\n393\t    <action>Provide the story file path and current status (now \"review\")</action>\n394\t\n395\t    <action>Based on {user_skill_level}, ask if user needs any explanations about:\n396\t      - What was implemented and how it works\n397\t      - Why certain technical decisions were made\n398\t      - How to test or verify the changes\n399\t      - Any patterns, libraries, or approaches used\n400\t      - Anything else they'd like clarified\n401\t    </action>\n402\t\n403\t    <check if=\"user asks for explanations\">\n404\t      <action>Provide clear, contextual explanations tailored to {user_skill_level}</action>\n405\t      <action>Use examples and references to specific code when helpful</action>\n406\t    </check>\n407\t\n408\t    <action>Once explanations are complete (or user indicates no questions), suggest logical next steps</action>\n409\t    <action>Recommended next steps (flexible based on project setup):\n410\t      - Review the implemented story and test the changes\n411\t      - Verify all acceptance criteria are met\n412\t      - Ensure deployment readiness if applicable\n413\t      - Run `code-review` workflow for peer review\n414\t      - Optional: If Test Architect module installed, run `/bmad:tea:automate` to expand guardrail tests\n415\t    </action>\n416\t\n417\t    <output>💡 **Tip:** For best results, run `code-review` using a **different** LLM than the one that implemented this story.</output>\n418\t    <check if=\"{sprint_status} file exists\">\n419\t      <action>Suggest checking {sprint_status} to see project progress</action>\n420\t    </check>\n421\t    <action>Remain flexible - allow user to choose their own path or ask for other assistance</action>\n422\t  </step>\n423\t\n424\t</workflow>\n425\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01HNbP4Hg5VKRrkree5HJepQ","session_id":"aeb5b1ee-06a7-4bdc-8279-6cd22d306d14","uuid":"eab001b6-7030-4ea8-a356-fb3c9673dde0","timestamp":"2026-04-02T10:46:15.419Z"}
