{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JWPSfMd9pChrXHMHYJCdbA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is clean. Here is the summary.\n\n---\n\n## Review Complete\n\n**Story Status:** verifying\n**Issues Found:** 1 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM, 3 LOW\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 HIGH, 3 MEDIUM (all HIGH and MEDIUM fixed)\n**Tests:** 26 passed (20 original + 6 new), full suite 3552 passed / 0 failed\n**Coverage:** 96.6% overall, all 148 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### What was fixed\n\n1. **H1 (namespace collision):** Renamed `readState`/`writeState` to `readWorkflowState`/`writeWorkflowState` in `src/lib/workflow-state.ts`, updated all tests and AGENTS.md to match. This prevents import conflicts with the existing `state.ts` module that exports identically-named functions.\n\n2. **M1 (tasks_completed element validation):** Added per-element shape validation in `isValidWorkflowState()` — checks `task_name`, `story_key`, `completed_at` are strings and optional `session_id` is string if present.\n\n3. **M2 (evaluator_scores + score_history element validation):** Added per-element validation for `evaluator_scores` (all 6 required fields typed) and `score_history` (all elements must be numbers).\n\n4. **M3 (missing validation tests):** Added 6 new tests covering: invalid element types in `tasks_completed`, missing required fields in `tasks_completed`, invalid element types in `evaluator_scores`, missing number fields in `evaluator_scores`, non-number `score_history` elements, and a positive test confirming valid arrays pass.\n\n### Files modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/workflow-state.ts` — renamed exports, added array element validation\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/workflow-state.test.ts` — updated imports/calls for rename, added 6 validation tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/AGENTS.md` — updated export names in documentation table\n- `/Use